<div id="banner">
	<h1>Vote Hank Perritt</h1>
</div>

<div class="content">
<p><a href="http://www.perrittforcongress.com/">Hank Perritt</a> is the democratic candidate in my district, running against incumbent Mark Kirk, <a href="http://www.clw.org/election/2002profiles/perritt.html">a strong advocate of missile defense</a>. Lessig has <a href="http://cyberlaw.stanford.edu/lessig/blog/archives/2002_08.shtml#000386">called Hank his hero</a> and &#8220;grandfather of cyberspace law&#8221;. Hank seems to be very smart and mostly in agreement with me. This is a district that votes democratic (voted for Al Gore in the last election) and the only reason Kirk succeed was because he&#8217;s an extremely moderate republican (pro-environment, pro-freedom-of-religion, etc.). I think if we could get the word out, Hank could have a real chance of winning here. I definitely have to investigate this.</p>

<p class="posted">posted August 21, 2002 05:47 PM (<a class="category" href="http://www.aaronsw.com/weblog/cat_politics">Politics</a>)  <a href="000522" rel="bookmark">#</a></p>
</div>

